x10.matrix

Class DenseMatrix

  • x10.lang.Object
    • x10.matrix.Matrix
      • x10.matrix.DenseMatrix

  • public class DenseMatrix
extends Matrix
    The dense matrix has all elements stored in column major order in a continuous memory space. Current implementation defines element using double type.

    • Field Detail

      • d

        public final x10.array.Array<x10.lang.Double> d
        Field Type: x10.array.Array[x10.lang.Double]{self.rail==true, self.rank==1}
        The storage for dense matrix is 1-dimension array.
Rational:
1) Compatible to column-major matrix storage specification, so that
the memory trunk can be passed to/from other program directly without conversion.
2) Fast access to data adjacent in the same column
